{"word":"G2896 - κράζω - krázō - krad'-zo - Cry","slug":"G2896","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">κράζω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>krázō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>krad'-zo"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cry"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BA;&#x03C1;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03B6;&#x03C9; - krazo&#x0304;</b> - <i>krad'-zo</i><p/>A primary verb; properly to &ldquo;croak&rdquo; (as a raven) or <i>scream</i>, that is, (generally) to <i>call</i> aloud (<i>shriek</i>, <i>exclaim</i>, <i>intreat</i>): - cry (out)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2905\">G2905</a>, <a href=\"#/G2906\">G2906</a>, <a href=\"#/G349\">G349</a>"}]}